Talks between Kim Yong Il and Nguyen Tan Dung Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hanoi, October 27 (KCNA-Correspondent) -- Talks were held between Kim Yong Il, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, and Nguyen Tan Dung, Prime Minister of Vietnam, in Hanoi Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the talks from the DPRK side were Kim Yong Il and Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Ri Kyong Sik, minister of Agriculture, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and Ma Chol Su, DPRK ambassador to Vietnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the Vietnamese side were Nguyen Tan Dung and Nguyen Xuan Phuc, chief of the General Office of the government, Hoang Tuan Anh, minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism, Vu Huy Hoang, minister of Industry and Commerce, Cao Duc Phat, minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Nguyen Van Tho, deputy minister of Foreign Affairs, an assistant to the prime minister and Le Van Cu, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK.  At the talks both sides exchanged views on boosting the bilateral relations by carrying forward the tradition of friendship between the two countries provided by President Kim Il Sung and the respected leader of the Vietnamese people Ho Chi Minh and supporting and cooperating with each other in the efforts to accomplish the cause of socialism and issues of mutual concern and reached a consensus on the matters taken up. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a sincere and friendly atmosphere.

Plan for Exchange between Governments of DPRK and Vietnam Inked  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hanoi, October 27 (KCNA-Correspondent) -- A 2008-2010 Plan for Exchange in Culture, Arts, Science and Education between the governments of the DPRK and Vietnam was signed in Hanoi on Oct. 27. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the signing ceremony from the DPRK side were Kim Yong Il, premier of the Cabinet, Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Ri Kyong Sik, minister of Agriculture, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and Ma Chol Su, DPRK ambassador to Vietnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the Vietnamese side were Nguyen Tan Dung, Prime Minister of Vietnam, Nguyen Xuan Phuc, chief of the General Office of the government, Hoang Tuan Anh, minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism, Vu Huy Hoang, minister of Industry and Commerce, Cao Duc Phat, minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Nguyen Van Tho, deputy minister of Foreign Affairs, an assistant to the prime minister of the government and Le Van Cu, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The plan was inked by Mun Jae Chol and Hoang Tuan Anh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A MOU on the cooperation in the field of agricultural science and technology was signed between the Ministry of Agriculture of the DPRK and the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development of Vietnam on the same day.

Inter-Sector Talks Held between DPRK and Vietnam  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hanoi, October 27 (KCNA-Correspondent) -- Inter-sector talks between the DPRK and Vietnam took place in Hanoi on Oct. 27. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks were separately held between Minister of Agriculture Ri Kyong Sik and Cao Duc Phat, minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, and between Acting Chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol and Hoang Tuan Anh, minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on boosting the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries in different fields as desired by the two peoples and issues of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendship atmosphere.

Vietnamese Government Hosts Banquet for Premier of DPRK Cabinet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hanoi, October 27 (KCNA-Correspondent) -- The Vietnamese government hosted a banquet on Oct. 27 in honor of Kim Yong Il, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, on an official goodwill visit to Vietnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Kim Yong Il and Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Ri Kyong Sik, minister of Agriculture, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and other suite members and Ambassador Ma Chol Su and staff members of the DPRK embassy in Hanoi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Vietnamese Prime Minister Nguyen Tan Dung and Chief of the General Office of the government Nguyen Xuan Phuc, Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism Hoang Tuan Anh, Minister of Industry and Commerce Vu Huy Hoang, Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development Cao Duc Phat, Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs Nguyen Van Tho, an assistant to the prime minister, Vietnamese Ambassador to the DPRK Le Van Cu and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nguyen Tan Dung in a speech recalled that the relations of friendship between Vietnam and the DPRK were provided by President Ho Chi Minh and President Kim Il Sung, noting that these relations have developed in the interests of the two peoples in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed sincere thanks to the DPRK government and people for rendering precious support to the Vietnamese people in their revolutionary cause.  He expressed belief that the fraternal Korean people would achieve greater success in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation under the leadership of General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Il in a speech expressed hope that the friendly Vietnamese government and people would register greater achievements in their work to build a rich and powerful state, while adhering to socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government and people of the DPRK will, in the future, too, make positive efforts to invariably carry forward and develop the good tradition of solidarity and cooperation between the peoples of the two countries, he stressed.

Namibian Government Delegation Here 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- A Namibian government delegation led by Defence Minister Charles D. N. P. Namoloh arrived here Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A welcome function took place before the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minister of the People's Armed Forces Kim Il Chol and Charles D. N. P. Namoloh reviewed a guard of honor of the Korean People's Army.

Kim Il Chol Meets Namibian Government Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol who is minister of the People's Armed Forces met and had a talk with the Namibian government delegation headed by Charles D. N. P. Namoloh, minister of Defence, on Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Pak Jae Gyong, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The defence minister conveyed to Kim Il Chol a personal letter of Namibian President Hifikepunye Pohamba to Kim Jong Il.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Namibian Defence Ministry 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the Defence Ministry of the Republic of Namibia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was handed to Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol who is minister of the People's Armed Forces by Defence Minister Charles D. N. P. Namoloh on Saturday.

Floral Tribute Paid to Revolutionary Martyrs by Namibian Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 28 (KCNA) -- A wreath in the name of a Namibian government delegation headed by Defence Minister of Namibia Charles D. N. P. Namoloh was laid before the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the wreath were letters "Glory to Revolutionary Martyrs!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The guests observed a moment's silence in memory of the revolutionary martyrs who fought for the liberation of Korea, socialist construction and the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche all their lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They placed bouquets before the bust of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.

Namibian Government Delegation Feted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 28 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Ministry of the People's Armed Forces hosted a banquet Saturday in honor of the visiting Namibian government delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were members of the delegation headed by Defence Minister Charles D. N. P. Namoloh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol who is minister of the People's Armed Forces, and Vice-Minister of the People's Armed Forces Pak Jae Gyong and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Chol in his speech made at the banquet said that the DPRK visit paid by the Namibian government delegation is an expression of solidarity with the army and people of the DPRK who have waged a vigorous struggle for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation and national reunification, true to the Songun leadership of Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that the delegation's visit would mark a good occasion in boosting the long-standing friendly and cooperative relations between the armies and peoples of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Namibian defence minister in a speech expressed thanks to the army and people of the DPRK for the kind hospitality accorded to the delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing thanks to the DPRK government for rendering sincere aid to Namibia during its struggle for national liberation, he said that the friendly and cooperative relations between Namibia and the DPRK have steadily developed under the deep care of the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He hoped that the Korean people would register greater success in the future, too.

DPRK Reiterates Closer Cooperation with UNESCO 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government will as ever boost the cooperation with the UNESCO and all its member nations, guided by the idea of the foreign policy of independence, peace and friendship and make a positive contribution to the international efforts for the materialization of its new mid-term strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The head of the DPRK delegation said this, when addressing the 34th plenary session of the general conference of the UNESCO on Oct. 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the UNESCO is performing its mission at a required level as the world's important intellectual body promoting and coordinating the development of fields including education, science and culture through the implementation of its mid-term strategy, he added that the DPRK has taken an active part in the activities of the UNESCO as its member state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important in carrying out the 2008-2013 mid-term strategy is to give priority to ensuring its effectiveness, he held, stressing that most of the development goals internationally agreed upon should be achieved and substantial results be attained in the period of the mid-term strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need for the UNESCO to make a constructive involvement in the process to reform the UN on the principle of firmly preserving its characteristics as an intellectual body and intensify its activities in the field of culture in a bid to contribute to the sustainable development and encourage in practice the speedy transfer of science and technology needed for this to the developing countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Appreciating the UNESCO for having paid due attention to the issue of preserving and protecting cultural treasures, he emphasized that it is an important issue in achieving reconciliation among nations and ensuring global peace and security to take international measures to ensure that the cultural treasures illegally taken away in the last periods including the Second World War are returned to those countries to which they belonged.

Greetings to Turkmenian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Turkmenian President Gurbankuli Berdimuhammedov on Saturday on the occasion of the national day of Turkmenistan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the message, Kim wished the Turkmenian people progress, prosperity and welfare and expressed belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to favorably develop.

Congratulations to Moroccan Prime Minister 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 28 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Il, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, sent a congratulatory message to Abbas El Fassi on his appointment as Moroccan Prime Minister. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the peoples of the two countries would grow stronger in the mutual interests, the message wished him success in his work for the prosperity of the country.

Congratulations to Palestinian Foreign Minister
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- DPRK Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun sent a congratulatory message to Riad Malki upon his appointment as foreign minister of the Palestinian National Authority. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing belief that the friendly relations between the two countries would continue to grow stronger, the message wished the Palestinian foreign minister success in his new job.

National Meeting of WPK Cell Secretaries Closes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- The national meeting of secretaries of the cells of the Workers' Party of Korea closed Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More speeches were made at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers said that thanks to the Songun guidance of Kim Jong Il the authority and prestige of the WPK have remarkably risen and the dignity and might of the country and the nation have been fully demonstrated before the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They vowed to carry the Songun cause of the party to completion by more firmly strengthening all the cells as the vanguard organizations upholding the Songun idea and line of Kim Jong Il in the van in hearty response to the militant tasks set forth in the congratulatory message of the WPK Central Committee.

Women's Football Rapidly Developed in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- The DPRK team won the gold medal at the 4th Asian Women's U-19 Football Championship held in China some time ago, thus further consolidating its unchallenged position in Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the women's football is not so long in Korea. But, since making its debut in international women's football arena, the DPRK has proved successful in various forms of soccer games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The might of the DPRK's women's football has been fully demonstrated in the 2000s.
 The DPRK came first at the 13th Asian Women's Football Championship in December Juche 90 (2001), and won the gold medals at the Albena Cup International Women's Football Championship and in the women's football event of the 14th Asian Games in 2002. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also took the first place at the 14th Asian Women's Football Championship in June 2003 and in the women's football event of the 15th Asian Games in 2006. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK team snatched the title in the 3rd FIFA U-20 Women's World Championship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though the DPRK team advanced into the quarter-finals at the 5th Women's World Cup, the Korean women footballers are bracing themselves up to register greater successes in the forthcoming international games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Very promising is the DPRK's women's football.

Repeal of Japan's Decision to Extend Sanctions against DPRK Demanded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- Noboru Kameda, representative of the Society of the Japan-Korea Culture, on a visit to the DPRK was interviewed by KCNA here Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He said that the Japanese government's decision to extend sanctions against the DPRK including the total embargo on its ships is wrong behavior swimming against the trend of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Declaration for the Development of North-South Relations and Peace and Prosperity was published in October this year in the wake of the publication of the North-South Joint Declaration on June 15, 2000, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world peace-loving people hail the publication of the Declaration for the Development of North-South Relations and Peace and Prosperity and hope for an early independent and peaceful reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today Japan-DPRK relations are not developing in the basic spirit of the Japan-DPRK Pyongyang Declaration. The Japanese government is not opting to improve the bilateral relations under the pretext of the "abduction issue". This is affecting the resumption of the talks for the establishment of the Japan-DPRK diplomatic relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese government should apologize and compensate for the unspeakable sufferings and pain imposed upon the Korean people in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the present Japanese government has not yet abandoned its wrong attitude toward the past wrongs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I cannot repress resentment at preceding Dietmen's visits to the "Yasukuni Shrine" and Japanese rightwing organizations' moves to distort history textbooks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only when the abnormal relations between Japan and the DPRK are brought to the earliest possible end, can the two countries become near and close countries, not near yet distant countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Society for the Japan-Korea Culture strongly demands the Japanese government give up its hostile policy toward the DPRK and retract its decision to extend the sanctions against the DPRK including a total embargo on the ship "Mangyongbong-92." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will in the future, too, extend invariable support and encouragement to the struggle to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea, promote Japan-DPRK friendship and protect the rights and national education of Koreans in Japan.

Decision to Extend Presence of S. Korean Troops in Iraq Opposed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 28 (KCNA) -- "National assemblymen" from the Democratic Labor Party of south Korea reportedly called an emergency press conference on Oct. 23 in opposition to a decision made by the authorities to extend the presence of troops in Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the conference the speakers accused the authorities of persistently trying to extend the presence of the troops while insisting on "cooperation" with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The authorities are resorting to such a hackneyed trick as calling for reducing the troops instead of extending their presence but this will invite stronger protest of the people, they held. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Grand National Party of south Korea and Ri Myong Bak will certainly be punished by the people as they support the U.S. moves to extend the presence of the troops, oft-repeating "war alliance" with it, they warned.

Actions Declared for Victory of Progressives in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration, the Solidarity of Youth and Students for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration and the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils reportedly declared 60-day all-out actions for the victory of the progressives in the "presidential elections" with due ceremony in Seoul on Oct. 20. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers at the ceremony called for eliminating those forces opposed to the June 15 joint declaration without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A declaration read out there said that the coming "presidential elections" are a fierce showdown between the forces for progressive reforms and the pro-U.S. conservatives, adding that the reunification forces supporting the June 15 joint declaration, the forces for progressive reforms should win a victory in the elections without fail in order to achieve independent reunification and national prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underlining the need to concentrate all efforts on enabling the progressive camp to emerge victorious in the elections, the declaration noted that it is the action goal to be attained by it under any circumstances to prevent the Grand National Party of south Korea from coming to power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration called on all the people to turn out as one in the campaign to punish the GNP opposed to the reunification and stage a dynamic anti-U.S. and anti-conservative struggle under the banner of the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, the above-mentioned organizations formed "headquarters for the campaign to implement the June 15 joint declaration".

Kim Jong Il's Works Off Press in Ecuador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 28 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il's famous works "Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy" and "On the Fundamentals of Revolutionary Party Building" were brought out in booklet by the Voluntad Publishing House in Ecuador on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 81st anniversary of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work "Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy", published on July 26, Juche 85 (1996), clearly indicates the limitation of the time the preceding philosophy was enunciated, gives scientific analysis of the originality of the Juche philosophy and expounds the idea that the Juche philosophy serves as revolutionary philosophy, political philosophy of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also gives principled issues arising in study and dissemination of the Juche philosophy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work "On the Fundamentals of Revolutionary Party Building", published on Oct. 10, Juche 81 (1992), clarifies the historical lesson drawn from the building of ruling parties in socialist countries, fundamental principle of building revolutionary party of Juche and issues concerning international unity and solidarity among revolutionary parties.

Important Days of DPRK Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 28 (KCNA) -- Korean book, photo and handicraft exhibitions were held in Mexico, Nigeria and a lecture in Guinea from Oct. 5 to 16 on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 81st anniversary of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the Korean book, photo and handicraft exhibitions were works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos showing the exploits performed by them, books and photos introducing Songun Korea and handicraft reflecting the creative talents of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of the cultural department of a city of Mexico State of Mexico, addressing the opening ceremony of the exhibition, said that the Workers' Party of Korea holding Kim Jong Il in high esteem as its general secretary has led Korean people to victory, happiness and glory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The special adviser to the president of Nigeria who is secretary in charge of social development of the Ministry of Federal Capital Territory noted at a ceremony of opening a week of Korean photo exhibition that the WPK and the Korean people have won great victories, successfully overcoming trials and difficulties under the outstanding Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The chief of the Guinean Group for the Study of February 16 Art who is general director of the office of copyright ownership in the lecture stressed that today a large number of WPK members are possessed of the spirit of devotedly defending the leader and transparent awareness of independence against imperialism as displayed by the members of the DIU 80-odd years ago, adding that the WPK is giving a steady continuity to the tradition of the DIU under the leadership of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.

WPK Founding Anniversary Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 27 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in Russia, Moldova and Guinea from Oct. 8 to 11 on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meetings were figures and members of the International Alliance of Societies for the Study of the Juche Idea and Songun Policy in East European and Central Asian Regions, the All-Russia Society for the Study and Dissemination of Kimilsungism, the Russian Youth Society for the Study of the Songun Policy, the Russian Society for the Promotion of the Study and Dissemination of Comrade Kim Jong Il's Works and the Russian Women's Union Named after Kim Jong Suk, the Moldovan Songun Youth Union for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Kim Il Sung Institute of Agricultural Science in Guinea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reports and speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mikhail Panchenko, general secretary of the international alliance, referred in detail to the glorious history of the WPK which has always emerged victorious under the wise guidance of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, saying that the world people struggling against imperialism under the present situation should learn from the practical experience of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Oleg Vernik, chairman of the Moldovan union, noted that they should advance along the road of independence in order to achieve the development of the country, underscoring the importance of applying the Juche idea to Moldova. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Malik Souma, director of the Guinean institute, said that the WPK having Kim Jong Il as its General Secretary has demonstrated its name as vanguard for accomplishing the cause of independence against imperialism worldwide, adding the WPK powerfully encourages the above-said cause with the Songun idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings.

Japan-Korea Educational Seminar Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, October 25 (KNS-KCNA) -- The 9th Japan-Korea educational seminar took place in Tokyo on Oct. 20. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were figures of the Japan Teachers' Union, Japan-Korea Society for Scientific and Educational Interchange, the Union of Korean Teachers and School Clerks in Japan and their members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floor was taken by Norio Fukuoka, director of the organizational department of the Japan Teachers' Union, Ku Tae Sok, chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the Union of Korean Teachers and School Clerks in Japan, and Kiyoo Nakagoji, chairman of the Japan-Korea Society for Scientific and Educational Interchange. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Speakers recalled that the suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and the Koreans in Japan is still going on in Japan though there is no more the Abe regime which persistently pursued its hostile policy toward the DPRK at a time when fresh progress is made in the relations between the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed a report and speeches by several figures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal adopted at the seminar stressed the need for the Japanese government to settle its inglorious past and resume the talks for the establishment of diplomatic ties according to the Japan-DPRK Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal called for expanding the scope of exchange to help Korean schools, fully guaranteeing the right of Koreans in Japan to their national education, respecting the implementation of their teaching programs including the study tour of their homeland by students of Korean schools and conducting a nationwide movement for the establishment of diplomatic ties between Japan and the DPRK.

Gobierno coreano se esforzara por realizar nueva estrategia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 27 de octubre (ATCC) -- En el futuro tambien, de acuerdo con el ideal de la politica exterior de la independencia, la paz y la amistad, el gobierno de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea fortalecera aun mas la cooperacion con la Organizacion de las Naciones Unidas para la Educacion, la Ciencia y la Cultura (UNESCO) y con todos sus miembros y contribuira activamente a los esfuerzos internacionales por la realizacion de la nueva estrategia a medio plazo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Afirmo asi el jefe de la delegacion coreana en su discurso pronunciado el dia 22 en el 34o pleno de la Asamblea General de la UNESCO. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el proceso de la ejecucion de la estrategia a medio plazo la UNESCO cumple debidamente su mision de importante organizacion intelectual mundial para acelerar y coordinar el desarrollo de los dominios de la educacion, ciencia y cultura, subrayo el e hizo constar que la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea participa activamente en las actividades como pais miembro de la UNESCO. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Dijo que la estrategia a medio plazo 2008-2013 debe prestar su primordial atencion a asegurar su eficiencia e insistio que en este periodo debe ser alcanzada la mayoria de las metas de desarrollo acordada internacionalmente y obtenidos los logros reales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La UNESCO debe participar de manera constructiva en el proceso de la reforma de la ONU en el principio de mantener viva la caracteristica de la organizacion intelectual, contribuir al desarrollo sostenido mediante el fortalecimiento de las actividades del dominio cultural y promover de manera practica el problema de transferir con rapidez los logros cientifico-tecnicos necesarios a los paises en vias de desarrollo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Luego de senalar que la UNESCO presta debida atencion al problema de la conservacion y la proteccion de bienes culturales enfatizo que tomar las medidas internacionales para la devolucion a los paises respectivos de los bienes culturales trasladados ilegalmente en el periodo de la Segunda Guerra Mundial y otros tiempos transcurridos deviene un problema importante en promover la reconciliacion entre las naciones, la paz y la seguridad del mundo.

Inaugurada Conferencia Nacional de Secretarios de Celula del Partido
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 27 de octubre (ATCC) -- Quedo iniciada el dia 26 en la capitalina Casa Cultural 25 de Abril la Conferencia Nacional de Secretarios de Celula del Partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el conclave participaron el miembro del Buro Politico del Comite Central del Partido del Trabajo de Corea Kim Yong Nam, los miembros suplentes del Buro Politico del CC del PTC Choe Thae Bok, Choe Yong Rim, Hong Song Nam y Hong Sok Hyong, los secretarios del CC del PTC Kim Kuk Thae, Kim Jung Rin y Kim Ki Nam, los funcionarios responsables del partido en el centro y las provincias, los ejemplares secretarios de celula del partido y otros funcionarios partidistas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El foro va a hacer balance de los exitos y experiencias logrados durante mas de 10 anos pasados en el desarrollo de las celulas del partido y discutir las tareas y medios para hacer que todas las celulas del partido cumplan con su mision y deber de vanguardia que apoya con fidelidad la causa del PTC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ante todo, Kim Yong Nam dio lectura al mensaje de felicitacion del CC del PTC dirigido a los participantes en la conferencia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El mensaje senala que el presente conclave es una conferencia de gran significado, que servira de un importante motivo para impulsar energicamente la marcha general de la revolucion del Songun (priorizacion militar), al manifestar el invencible poderio del PTC que bajo la gran bandera del Songun condujo a la victoria la causa de construccion del partido del Juche y la del socialismo, elevar la funcion y el papel de las celulas del partido conforme a la demanda del partido y la revolucion en desarrollo, y producir un viraje trascendental en toda la labor del partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El CC del PTC evalua altamente que los participantes en la conferencia y todos los secretarios de celula del partido del pais entero hicieron un gran aporte a la lucha por fortalecer el partido y las filas revolucionarias, defender con firmeza el socialismo al estilo coreano y lograr la prosperidad de la patria, subraya el mensaje y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  "!Convirtamos todas las celulas del partido en las organizaciones vanguardistas que apoyan con fidelidad la direccion de nuestro partido sobre la revolucion mediante el Songun!", esta es la consigna combativa a ser sostenida por las celulas del partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   El CC del PTC esta bien convencido de que los participantes en el foro y todos los secretarios de celula del partido de todo el pais apoyarian fielmente la direccion del camarada Kim Jong Il sobre la revolucion mediante el Songun y elevarian la funcion y papel combativos de las celulas del partido para asi contribuir activamente al fortalecimiento y desarrollo del PTC y al cumplimiento de la causa de la construccion de la gran potencia prospera socialista. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El informe de la ocasion estuvo a cargo de Choe Yong Rim, quien dijo en particular: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los primeros dias de la lucha revolucionaria antijaponesa, el Presidente Kim Il Sung presento la original teoria de construccion del partido a base de la idea Juche, organizo primero la organizacion de base del partido y, a manera de ampliarla y fortalecerla, fundo un partido revolucionario. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La idea, la teoria y las proezas de orientacion del Presidente para el fortalecimiento de las celulas del partido se llevan adelante por el respetado camarada Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los primeros tiempos de su orientacion al PTC y la revolucion coreana, el Dirigente sistematizo integralmente la idea Juche y la teoria de construccion del partido jucheano y aclaro el rumbo y los medios para el fortalecimiento de las celulas del partido, organizacion de base del partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas, en su curso de orientacion a muchas celulas del partido preparo un brillante modelo en la labor de las celulas del partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente condujo sabiamente el trabajo para convertir todas las celulas del partido en las de fidelidad y llevo a una nueva etapa la lucha historica por fortalecer el PTC en el eterno partido del Presidente Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La historica carta enviada el 10 de mayo del 80 (1991) de la Era Juche a los participantes en el cursillo nacional de los secretarios de celula del partido "Fortalezcamos las celulas del partido" resulta un gran programa que debe ser mantenido siempre por todas las celulas del partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A lo largo de este ultimo decenio que data de la conferencia de secretarios de celula de todo el partido, las celulas del partido se han fortalecido en las puras entes ideologicas que comparten la ideologia y el proposito con la Direccion de la Revolucion y han glorificado su honor de poderoso fundamento para la defensa del socialismo y ejecutor de la politica del partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La tarea general que se presenta ante las celulas del partido es agrupar compactamente a todos los militantes y otros trabajadores en torno al Dirigente y llamarlos energicamente a la marcha general para conquistar las altas metas de la construccion de la gran potencia prospera socialista siguiendo a la direccion del partido sobre la revolucion mediante el Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las celulas del partido deben actuar con la meta mas alta conveniente a la demanda del nuevo siglo para consolidar todas las celulas del partido en las filas revolucionarias infinitamente fieles al Dirigente y contribuir activamente a elevar la funcion y papel combativos del partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
